Moreover, the adoption of household robots is not only limited to traditional tasks like cleaning but is expanding to include a broader range of applications such as security surveillance, pet care, and even companion robots for the elderly. This diversification of functionalities is opening up new avenues for market players to innovate and cater to evolving consumer needs. For instance, the development of advanced sensors, machine learning algorithms, and autonomous navigation systems is enabling household robots to perform tasks with greater precision and efficiency, further driving their adoption across different segments.

